      "content": "Even a small amount of alcohol while on metronidazole can still pose a risk of a mild reaction, such as an upset stomach. However, it's unlikely to be a medical emergency, but it can still be uncomfortable. To be completely safe, it's best to avoid alcohol until your medication is fully out of your system. Your health is worth the inconvenience, and no real occasion should be worth risking any potential side effects. Enjoy your dinner and stay healthy!",
